Capitec Bank Holdings Ltd. (CPI) , a South
African lender, fell for the first day in eight after reporting
earnings that missed analystsâ€™ expectations.  The stock retreated as much as 7.4 percent to 157.41 rand
and traded 1.8 percent down at 167 rand at 10:17 a.m. in
Johannesburg.  Capitec said profit for the year through February climbed
47 percent to 640 million rand, missing a 652 million-rand
median estimate by two analysts polled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
